<p>I have a table with columns like </p>  <pre><code>insertTimeStamp, port, data 1              , 20  , 'aaa' 2              , 20  , 'aba' 3              , 20  , '3aa' 4              , 20  , 'aab' 2              , 21  , 'aza' 5              , 21  , 'aha' 8              , 21  , 'aaa' 15             , 22  , '2aa' </code></pre>  <p>Now I need <em>N</em> Rows (Say 4) from that table, ordered asc by <code>insertTimeStamp</code>. But if possible, I want to get them from different <code>port</code>s.</p>  <p>So the result should be:</p>  <pre><code>1              , 20  , 'aaa' 2              , 20  , 'aba' 2              , 21  , 'aza' 15             , 22  , '2aa' </code></pre>  <p>If there are not enough different values in <code>port</code> I would like select the remaining ones with the lowest <code>insertTimeStamp</code>.</p>